A Bash script refers to a text file containing series of commands that can be executed to achieve desired results.
To create a bash script first create a file for instance touch random.sh
open the file and enter
 #!/bin/bash
# this script just echoes Hello world
echo "Hello world"
 then run the following commands on the CLi
 ls -l random.sh
 chmod u+x random.sh
 ./random.sh
 then run the script.
